1️⃣ What is Express.js?

👉 Express.js is a fast, minimal web framework for Node.js used to build APIs and web applications.

2️⃣ Why use Express.js?

👉

Simplifies routing
Middleware support
Easy API creation
Better structure than core Node.js
3️⃣ How to install Express?
npm install express
4️⃣ Basic Express Server Example
const express = require('express');
const app = express();

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
    res.send("Hello World");
});

app.listen(3000);
5️⃣ What is routing in Express?

👉 Mapping URLs + HTTP methods to specific functions.
